author: LYNSI BURTON, SEATTLEPI.COM STAFF
title: State emergency: Nickelback coming to state fair
text:
If you smell something dank around Puyallup at the end of this summer, it's not the Tacoma Aroma -- it's chewing tobacco-flavored moose jerky acting as a rock band called Nickelback.
That's right: The epitome of the name "Chad" is kicking off the concert series for the Washington State Fair (which native continue to stubbornly call "The Puyallup").
They're the second act announced for the fair, after bloated barfly Jason Aldean, who's set to close out the series.
If you want to shell out $80+ on self-loathing or your worst enemy, Nickelback tickets go on sale Feb. 11.
Also find dozens of better alternatives of Washington-bound acts in the gallery.
